1
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:32,311
Ah!

2
00:00:32,311 --> 00:00:34,847
Kanaris, it seems that you've
made the mistake of letting

3
00:00:34,847 --> 00:00:36,494
your position go to your head.

4
00:00:36,494 --> 00:00:37,501
No.

5
00:00:37,501 --> 00:00:39,931
You may work quickly, but at
times it causes me displeasure.

6
00:00:39,931 --> 00:00:43,571
Don't be foolish enough to think
your position makes you immune.

7
00:00:43,571 --> 00:00:46,051
Being a keeper of the Heaven's
Blade will not save you,

8
00:00:46,051 --> 00:00:47,491
do you understand me?

9
00:00:47,491 --> 00:00:51,291
I'll kill every last
one of you if I have to.

10
00:00:51,291 --> 00:00:53,771
Please forgive
me, Your Majesty.

11
00:00:53,771 --> 00:00:56,771
Show mercy.

12
00:00:56,771 --> 00:01:01,251
(GASPING)

13
00:01:01,251 --> 00:01:04,251
THEME SONG: (SINGING) Brave
your truth and brave yourself,

14
00:01:04,251 --> 00:01:09,731
so we can go somewhere
with the dite.

15
00:01:09,731 --> 00:01:12,731
Keep hope alive, now we
want to find the new world.

16
00:01:18,211 --> 00:01:22,691
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

17
00:02:31,611 --> 00:02:33,771
All right, listen up.

18
00:02:33,771 --> 00:02:35,811
The next competition
is a big one.

19
00:02:35,811 --> 00:02:37,731
It's Vanze and
the first platoon.

20
00:02:37,731 --> 00:02:39,171
These guys are no joke.

21
00:02:39,171 --> 00:02:41,771
Still, I feel confident
that the 17th has

22
00:02:41,771 --> 00:02:44,171
a chance of winning this thing.

23
00:02:44,171 --> 00:02:47,131
That said, I've decided
to hold a training camp.

24
00:02:47,131 --> 00:02:48,611
We all ship out tomorrow.

25
00:02:48,611 --> 00:02:49,411
Hm?

26
00:02:49,411 --> 00:02:51,771
So where'd you come up with
that kind of dough anyway?

27
00:02:51,771 --> 00:02:54,531
It's my brother, and I'm
assuming he wants something

28
00:02:54,531 --> 00:02:56,171
inappropriate in return, right?

29
00:02:56,171 --> 00:02:57,011
No.

30
00:02:57,011 --> 00:02:59,491
This time the student council
president isn't involved.

31
00:02:59,491 --> 00:03:00,291
But don't worry.

32
00:03:00,291 --> 00:03:03,291
As far as the budget goes,
it's all taken care of.

33
00:03:03,291 --> 00:03:05,291
Well, it sounds good to me.

34
00:03:05,291 --> 00:03:07,931
I've got no problem
with cutting class.

35
00:03:07,931 --> 00:03:08,731
It's perfect.

36
00:03:08,731 --> 00:03:10,131
It'll give me the
extra time I need

37
00:03:10,131 --> 00:03:11,971
to finish adjusting the dites.

38
00:03:11,971 --> 00:03:13,011
You can count me in.

39
00:03:16,971 --> 00:03:19,411
Yeah, all right, as you wish.

40
00:03:19,411 --> 00:03:21,411
[LAUGHING]

41
00:03:26,371 --> 00:03:28,491
The plant area cleaning
units aren't working

42
00:03:28,491 --> 00:03:30,611
in the machinery department.

43
00:03:30,611 --> 00:03:32,371
This isn't good.

44
00:03:32,371 --> 00:03:35,051
We've received frequent
reports of this type of problem

45
00:03:35,051 --> 00:03:36,131
all across the city.

46
00:03:36,131 --> 00:03:38,171
It's the same with
people, isn't it?

47
00:03:38,171 --> 00:03:40,611
If you work them too hard,
they'll start to break down.

48
00:03:40,611 --> 00:03:42,851
If it were that simple,
I wouldn't have called you.

49
00:03:42,851 --> 00:03:45,131
I need the great
Vanze to save the day.

50
00:03:45,131 --> 00:03:47,451
Otherwise I would have
simply fixed it myself.

51
00:03:47,451 --> 00:03:48,971
What exactly does that mean?

52
00:03:48,971 --> 00:03:50,571
Something in my
gut tells me this

53
00:03:50,571 --> 00:03:52,491
is not simple deterioration.

54
00:03:52,491 --> 00:03:55,091
I believe that it's the will of
the city running amok, causing

55
00:03:55,091 --> 00:03:57,931
mass chaos and destruction.

56
00:03:57,931 --> 00:03:59,291
Are you suggesting
this is happening

57
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:00,611
because of the fallen one?

58
00:04:00,611 --> 00:04:04,051
If it is, we've taken on
something far more troublesome

59
00:04:04,051 --> 00:04:07,331
than I'd originally imagined.

60
00:04:07,331 --> 00:04:11,291
[STREETCAR BELL RINGING]

61
00:04:12,011 --> 00:04:12,771
Huh?

62
00:04:21,251 --> 00:04:24,691
[STREETCAR BRAKES]

63
00:04:32,651 --> 00:04:34,611
This place is huge.

64
00:04:34,611 --> 00:04:36,211
Yeah, the
agricultural students

65
00:04:36,211 --> 00:04:37,931
use it for overnight stays.

66
00:04:37,931 --> 00:04:39,411
This is also where
Zuellni's these food

67
00:04:39,411 --> 00:04:41,651
supply is grown and harvested.

68
00:04:41,651 --> 00:04:43,531
What took so long?

69
00:04:43,531 --> 00:04:44,691
Wait, she's here?

70
00:04:44,691 --> 00:04:47,451
Oh, sorry, but it
was part of the deal.

71
00:04:47,451 --> 00:04:49,931
In exchange for our lodging,
we had to agree to an article

72
00:04:49,931 --> 00:04:50,731
for "Weekly Look In."

73
00:04:50,731 --> 00:04:51,531
We're your sponsors.

74
00:04:51,531 --> 00:04:53,051
Isn't that great?

75
00:04:53,051 --> 00:04:54,131
And guess what?

76
00:04:54,131 --> 00:04:56,691
I'm the photographer, so I'm
gonna get some awesome shots.

77
00:04:56,691 --> 00:04:58,291
So that's what this is?

78
00:04:58,291 --> 00:04:59,571
I love good press.

79
00:04:59,571 --> 00:05:02,571
This trip just keeps
getting better.

80
00:05:02,571 --> 00:05:03,971
Look, I understand
the article.

81
00:05:03,971 --> 00:05:07,691
But can someone explain to me
what those two are doing here?

82
00:05:07,691 --> 00:05:09,611
Mayshen and I
and your helpers.

83
00:05:09,611 --> 00:05:10,971
We'll be taking care
of all the cooking

84
00:05:10,971 --> 00:05:13,131
and cleaning so you guys
can focus on the big match.

85
00:05:13,131 --> 00:05:14,251
Hey, thanks, guys.

86
00:05:14,251 --> 00:05:15,491
That's awesome.

87
00:05:21,691 --> 00:05:23,811
I am not pleased.

88
00:05:23,811 --> 00:05:27,011
This is a way too cramped.

89
00:05:27,011 --> 00:05:28,051
Restoration.

90
00:05:28,051 --> 00:05:28,811
All right.

91
00:05:28,811 --> 00:05:31,411
Layfee, enemy
targets at 6 o'clock.

92
00:05:31,411 --> 00:05:32,211
Copy that.

93
00:05:32,211 --> 00:05:34,011
Keep on pealing the potatoes.

94
00:05:34,011 --> 00:05:35,731
Yes, Roger that, Layfee.

95
00:05:35,731 --> 00:05:37,931
(GIGGLES)

96
00:05:37,931 --> 00:05:39,331
Need help?

97
00:05:39,331 --> 00:05:40,851
Ah!

98
00:05:40,851 --> 00:05:41,651
Layfee, I, uh‐‐

99
00:05:41,651 --> 00:05:45,851
I'm free till this
afternoon's training.

100
00:05:45,851 --> 00:05:47,331
Oh, thank you.

101
00:05:51,691 --> 00:05:52,931
Say, how come you're alone?

102
00:05:52,931 --> 00:05:54,131
Where is everyone?

103
00:05:54,131 --> 00:05:56,491
Oh, well, uh, Mifi's
doing her article,

104
00:05:56,491 --> 00:05:59,211
and Nari's off getting
ready for the training.

105
00:05:59,211 --> 00:06:04,371
Your platoon leader told her
she could use an extra hand.

106
00:06:04,371 --> 00:06:06,651
Isn't this a lot of work
for you to do on your own?

107
00:06:06,651 --> 00:06:07,491
Mm‐mm.

108
00:06:07,491 --> 00:06:10,571
To be completely honest
with you, I love to cook.

109
00:06:10,571 --> 00:06:12,571
Besides, it's the only
thing I'm good at.

110
00:06:12,571 --> 00:06:15,931
Hey, that's not true.

111
00:06:15,931 --> 00:06:18,291
I can almost hear them.

112
00:06:18,291 --> 00:06:19,731
A little closer‐‐

113
00:06:19,731 --> 00:06:21,691
You are so funny!

114
00:06:21,691 --> 00:06:23,051
Thanks, Mayshen.

115
00:06:23,051 --> 00:06:24,051
All right, I give up.

116
00:06:24,051 --> 00:06:26,691
My only option is to use neni.

117
00:06:26,691 --> 00:06:28,131
NINA: What's going on?

118
00:06:28,131 --> 00:06:28,931
Hey, Nina.

119
00:06:35,011 --> 00:06:36,771
Maybe we should help, huh?

120
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:38,171
Yes, I think you're right.

121
00:06:38,171 --> 00:06:40,971
Nina, do you even
know how to cook?

122
00:06:40,971 --> 00:06:42,611
Yeah, of course I do.

123
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:45,171
I make pancakes for Harley
once, and they were so good,

124
00:06:45,171 --> 00:06:49,291
he wept tears of joy
while he ate them.

125
00:06:49,291 --> 00:06:50,851
And what about you, Felli?

126
00:06:50,851 --> 00:06:54,731
Oh, trust me, I
know how to cook.

127
00:06:54,731 --> 00:06:58,651
[LAUGHTER]

128
00:07:00,651 --> 00:07:02,651
(LAUGHING).

129
00:07:02,651 --> 00:07:03,851
What is it?

130
00:07:03,851 --> 00:07:06,771
(LAUGHING) Oh, nothing,
just think of how silly

131
00:07:06,771 --> 00:07:08,811
you two look.

132
00:07:08,811 --> 00:07:10,611
I have something
to show you guys.

133
00:07:10,611 --> 00:07:15,691
Allow me to introduce you to the
greatest appliance ever made.

134
00:07:15,691 --> 00:07:16,811
And voila.
‐ Huh?

135
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:17,691
What the heck's that?

136
00:07:17,691 --> 00:07:19,371
A kitchen miracle!

137
00:07:19,371 --> 00:07:21,971
You'll be peeling the skins
off potatoes in no time.

138
00:07:21,971 --> 00:07:22,931
It's the best!

139
00:07:22,931 --> 00:07:24,771
What, such a thing exists?

140
00:07:24,771 --> 00:07:26,531
Give it to me now!

141
00:07:26,531 --> 00:07:28,411
Would you kindly
let go, please?

142
00:07:28,411 --> 00:07:29,251
No!

143
00:07:29,251 --> 00:07:31,331
I think you should
leave this one to me.

144
00:07:31,331 --> 00:07:33,411
Don't you think your time
would be better spent planning

145
00:07:33,411 --> 00:07:34,771
today's training regements?

146
00:07:34,771 --> 00:07:35,571
Oh, yeah?

147
00:07:35,571 --> 00:07:37,971
Well, why don't you give some
thought to your own training

148
00:07:37,971 --> 00:07:38,771
routine, huh?

149
00:07:38,771 --> 00:07:42,731
What the heck do I know
about being a neni operator?

150
00:07:42,731 --> 00:07:43,651
No need to worry.

151
00:07:43,651 --> 00:07:44,691
I've been doing this for years.

152
00:07:44,691 --> 00:07:45,771
What, you think I'm a rookie?

153
00:07:45,771 --> 00:07:48,371
What are you
two doing in here?

154
00:07:48,371 --> 00:07:49,171
Layfon!

155
00:07:49,171 --> 00:07:49,971
You looked kind of busy.

156
00:07:49,971 --> 00:07:52,011
So I thought I'd
lend a helping hand.

157
00:07:52,011 --> 00:07:54,811
Oh, thanks a lot, but
we've already finished up.

158
00:07:54,811 --> 00:07:56,411
Well, I got to go
change before dinner.

159
00:08:05,051 --> 00:08:06,451
Restoration.

160
00:08:09,331 --> 00:08:11,331
Sure enough, I think
it's much better to use

161
00:08:11,331 --> 00:08:12,811
a configuration you're used to.

162
00:08:12,811 --> 00:08:15,731
A capture rope, huh?

163
00:08:15,731 --> 00:08:16,651
Wow!

164
00:08:16,651 --> 00:08:18,091
The first day and
last appearance

165
00:08:18,091 --> 00:08:19,851
of Nari and the 17th platoon.

166
00:08:19,851 --> 00:08:21,931
I wouldn't be so
sure about that.

167
00:08:21,931 --> 00:08:24,051
Battle fatigues really suit her.

168
00:08:24,051 --> 00:08:26,451
I don't think I'd mind if she
stuck around a little longer.

169
00:08:26,451 --> 00:08:27,371
What do you say?

170
00:08:27,371 --> 00:08:29,131
Sorry, but I
already have my duties

171
00:08:29,131 --> 00:08:31,131
with the municipal police.

172
00:08:31,131 --> 00:08:33,651
That's fine.

173
00:08:33,651 --> 00:08:35,011
All right, guys,
let's train like this

174
00:08:35,011 --> 00:08:36,291
is a real competition.

175
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:37,691
How are we
supposed to do that?

176
00:08:37,691 --> 00:08:40,131
We don't have enough people
to make up two platoons.

177
00:08:40,131 --> 00:08:41,691
Oh, that's not a problem.

178
00:08:41,691 --> 00:08:42,491
Layfon‐‐

179
00:08:42,491 --> 00:08:43,291
Uh‐‐

180
00:08:43,291 --> 00:08:45,411
‐‐think you can
handle being alone?

181
00:08:45,411 --> 00:08:47,051
That's not fair to him.

182
00:08:47,051 --> 00:08:47,971
No way.

183
00:08:47,971 --> 00:08:50,491
It's gonna be four
against one! (GIGGLING)

184
00:08:50,491 --> 00:08:52,011
Hey, just give it a whirl.

185
00:08:52,011 --> 00:08:53,651
You'll see.

186
00:08:53,651 --> 00:08:54,451
Here we go.

187
00:08:58,571 --> 00:09:01,451
All right, guys, I'll go get the
flag, Naruki, you're the decoy.

188
00:09:01,451 --> 00:09:02,811
Sharnid, slow them down.

189
00:09:02,811 --> 00:09:04,331
And Felli, you
stay here with me.

190
00:09:04,331 --> 00:09:05,771
You got it?
‐ Yes, ma'am.

191
00:09:05,771 --> 00:09:06,651
Roger that.

192
00:09:20,091 --> 00:09:22,091
He's gone!

193
00:09:22,091 --> 00:09:24,091
FELLI (VOICEOVER): He's
approaching from behind.

194
00:09:24,091 --> 00:09:26,091
What?

195
00:09:26,091 --> 00:09:28,131
You don't have enough
can in your legs.

196
00:09:28,131 --> 00:09:28,931
Ah!

197
00:09:33,851 --> 00:09:36,811
[GRUNTING]

198
00:09:36,811 --> 00:09:38,491
I can't believe it.

199
00:09:38,491 --> 00:09:39,291
Layfon?

200
00:09:54,171 --> 00:09:57,771
I'll get him this time.

201
00:09:57,771 --> 00:09:58,611
Ah!

202
00:10:02,091 --> 00:10:04,731
Oh.

203
00:10:04,731 --> 00:10:05,531
Ah.

204
00:10:18,411 --> 00:10:20,451
[SIGH]

205
00:10:20,451 --> 00:10:22,691
Looks like Layfon won, huh?

206
00:10:22,691 --> 00:10:23,491
Oh.

207
00:10:39,611 --> 00:10:42,331
Wow, I guess my editor
was right all along.

208
00:10:42,331 --> 00:10:44,051
It's amazing, isn't it?

209
00:10:44,051 --> 00:10:45,611
He's more than talented.

210
00:10:45,611 --> 00:10:49,011
In Glendan, he was one of the
keepers of the Heaven's Blades.

211
00:10:49,011 --> 00:10:49,771
I don't get it.

212
00:10:49,771 --> 00:10:52,771
If he was that powerful,
why did he leave Glendan?

213
00:10:52,771 --> 00:10:55,811
Apparently, he
got in trouble, and

214
00:10:55,811 --> 00:10:57,491
so they forced him to leave.

215
00:10:57,491 --> 00:10:59,531
I don't think it was his choice.

216
00:10:59,531 --> 00:11:02,171
I didn't tell you this, but
my boss asked me to get dirt

217
00:11:02,171 --> 00:11:04,531
on Layfee for this article.

218
00:11:04,531 --> 00:11:06,451
Otherwise there'd be
no reason for "Weekly

219
00:11:06,451 --> 00:11:09,171
Look In" to pay for our
lodgings and foot the bill.

220
00:11:09,171 --> 00:11:10,851
Wait a minute, does
Nina know about this?

221
00:11:10,851 --> 00:11:11,651
No way.

222
00:11:17,411 --> 00:11:22,851
[GIGGLING]

223
00:11:28,371 --> 00:11:34,331
[WIND BLOWING]

224
00:11:40,030 --> 00:11:42,670
What is your
bidding, My Queen?

225
00:11:42,670 --> 00:11:45,310
The fallen one, that was
discovered in Zuellni‐‐

226
00:11:45,310 --> 00:11:46,950
I believe summoning
it to Glendan

227
00:11:46,950 --> 00:11:49,630
would be the best
possible course of action.

228
00:11:49,630 --> 00:11:51,510
Are you listening
to me, Your Majesty?

229
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:53,190
Yes, I hear you.

230
00:11:53,190 --> 00:11:55,510
There are no longer
12 Heaven's Blades now.

231
00:11:55,510 --> 00:11:58,470
And that which can be obtained
simply must be at any cost.

232
00:11:58,470 --> 00:12:00,470
When he first held his
blade, I was hopeful,

233
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:04,470
and I thought he'd finally
come to us at long last.

234
00:12:04,470 --> 00:12:07,870
But now I wonder if banishing
Layfon was a grave mistake.

235
00:12:07,870 --> 00:12:09,670
Heaven's Blades
and neni operators

236
00:12:09,670 --> 00:12:11,870
are inhuman in some
ways, and the people

237
00:12:11,870 --> 00:12:14,790
must remain ignorant of that
fact for their own protection.

238
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:16,230
We can never allow
them to realize

239
00:12:16,230 --> 00:12:17,550
what you're truly capable of.

240
00:12:20,830 --> 00:12:22,310
But what was I to do?

241
00:12:22,310 --> 00:12:24,630
What happened couldn't
be helped, could it?

242
00:12:24,630 --> 00:12:27,430
Though it does make
me sad for Leerin.

243
00:12:27,430 --> 00:12:28,830
I have something to report.

244
00:12:28,830 --> 00:12:29,630
You do?

245
00:12:33,790 --> 00:12:35,430
Wait, what is this?

246
00:12:35,430 --> 00:12:36,830
I don't understand it.

247
00:12:36,830 --> 00:12:38,750
Why did Glendan appear
before that girl?

248
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,470
It doesn't make any sense.

249
00:12:40,470 --> 00:12:41,350
It seems so strange.

250
00:12:55,910 --> 00:12:57,830
A contaminoid was
present, and you

251
00:12:57,830 --> 00:12:59,870
were also there, Your Majesty.

252
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:01,950
You should have been able
to defeat the contaminoid

253
00:13:01,950 --> 00:13:05,110
before Glendan intervened.

254
00:13:05,110 --> 00:13:08,750
But the fact remains, Glendan
did appear before that girl.

255
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:12,470
It seems as if the spirit
was trying to shield her.

256
00:13:12,470 --> 00:13:15,110
And that's why I
obtained some of her hair

257
00:13:15,110 --> 00:13:18,190
and had it analyzed.

258
00:13:18,190 --> 00:13:22,230
I discovered she's‐‐ (GASPING)

259
00:13:22,230 --> 00:13:25,350
Kanaris, it seems that you've
made the mistake of letting

260
00:13:25,350 --> 00:13:26,670
your position go to your head.

261
00:13:26,670 --> 00:13:27,430
No.

262
00:13:27,430 --> 00:13:31,350
You may work quickly, but at
times it causes me displeasure.

263
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:35,070
Don't be foolish enough to think
your position makes you immune.

264
00:13:35,070 --> 00:13:37,550
Being a keeper of the Heaven's
Blade will not save you.

265
00:13:37,550 --> 00:13:38,990
Do you understand me?

266
00:13:38,990 --> 00:13:42,710
I'll kill every last
one of you if I have to.

267
00:13:42,710 --> 00:13:45,230
Please forgive
me, Your Majesty.

268
00:13:45,230 --> 00:13:46,230
Show mercy.

269
00:13:51,190 --> 00:13:53,670
You're excused.

270
00:13:53,670 --> 00:13:56,150
[CRYING]

271
00:13:59,110 --> 00:14:02,110
Oh, wow, thank you, Mayshen.

272
00:14:02,110 --> 00:14:03,670
To be honest, I don't
think that I've ever

273
00:14:03,670 --> 00:14:05,550
eaten anything this delicious.

274
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:08,030
You really are an
incredible cook.

275
00:14:08,030 --> 00:14:09,350
[GASPING]

276
00:14:09,350 --> 00:14:11,470
Mm, wow, this is
really fantastic.

277
00:14:11,470 --> 00:14:13,870
I could never make
sandwiches like these.

278
00:14:13,870 --> 00:14:16,870
But I feel like I've had
this somewhere before.

279
00:14:16,870 --> 00:14:20,350
Oh, you have, huh?

280
00:14:20,350 --> 00:14:21,190
That's it!

281
00:14:21,190 --> 00:14:23,910
It's got the same flavor of
those meals you bring to work,

282
00:14:23,910 --> 00:14:25,950
the ones you always
share with me.

283
00:14:25,950 --> 00:14:26,750
Huh?

284
00:14:30,150 --> 00:14:32,110
[CRYING]

285
00:14:32,110 --> 00:14:32,990
Hold on a second.

286
00:14:32,990 --> 00:14:34,750
Are you the one who made those?

287
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:37,710
[GASP]

288
00:14:40,190 --> 00:14:41,190
[CRYING]

289
00:14:41,190 --> 00:14:41,990
Hey!

290
00:14:44,390 --> 00:14:46,870
People like Layfon are
different because they can use

291
00:14:46,870 --> 00:14:49,310
all different types of
K. That's why an Ottoman

292
00:14:49,310 --> 00:14:51,110
dite is usually your best bet.

293
00:14:51,110 --> 00:14:53,510
How a dite is made can
change its configuration.

294
00:14:53,510 --> 00:14:55,670
But even simple dites
are so intricate.

295
00:14:55,670 --> 00:14:56,990
Would you shut up?

296
00:14:56,990 --> 00:14:57,990
We're eating.

297
00:14:57,990 --> 00:14:58,790
Come on.

298
00:14:58,790 --> 00:15:00,630
I think dinner is the perfect
chance for us to talk.

299
00:15:00,630 --> 00:15:01,390
I swear!

300
00:15:01,390 --> 00:15:02,750
Ow!

301
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:04,230
NINA: You had that one coming!

302
00:15:04,230 --> 00:15:07,150
Seriously, I mean, how
thick are you, huh?

303
00:15:07,150 --> 00:15:08,790
Didn't you think
that was strange?

304
00:15:08,790 --> 00:15:10,230
Well?

305
00:15:10,230 --> 00:15:16,070
There's a limit to how
dense someone could be.

306
00:15:16,070 --> 00:15:18,390
And so do you think
Nina might like Layfon,

307
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:20,230
like more than just a friend?

308
00:15:20,230 --> 00:15:21,870
Why do you say that?

309
00:15:21,870 --> 00:15:22,750
And then there's Felli.

310
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:24,750
She might be into to him, too.

311
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:29,910
Mayshen, do you think
she even has a chance?

312
00:15:29,910 --> 00:15:31,070
Mayshen?

313
00:15:31,070 --> 00:15:34,190
Oh, hey, where were you?

314
00:15:34,190 --> 00:15:35,510
I'm really sorry.

315
00:15:35,510 --> 00:15:38,630
I'll finish the rest.

316
00:15:38,630 --> 00:15:40,390
Ugh, this is not good.

317
00:15:44,870 --> 00:15:46,510
I have to apologize to Mayshen.

318
00:15:53,710 --> 00:15:55,550
Mifi, stop.

319
00:15:55,550 --> 00:15:59,030
Please don't write that article.

320
00:15:59,030 --> 00:16:01,190
Nari, what are
you talking about?

321
00:16:01,190 --> 00:16:03,470
Today, when I
fought against Layfee,

322
00:16:03,470 --> 00:16:05,630
I honestly felt
my chest tighten.

323
00:16:05,630 --> 00:16:07,230
I felt like every
one of his moves

324
00:16:07,230 --> 00:16:10,870
held all the experiences
he's had up till now‐‐

325
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:18,150
beautifully, incredibly,
but with sadness.

326
00:16:18,150 --> 00:16:19,510
Guess I've always
sort of wondered

327
00:16:19,510 --> 00:16:23,150
what his past was really like.

328
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:24,430
All the more
reason to find out

329
00:16:24,430 --> 00:16:27,390
why Layfee had to leave Glendan,
even after becoming a keeper

330
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:28,630
of the Heaven's Blades.

331
00:16:28,630 --> 00:16:30,030
Come on, now, aren't
you just dying

332
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:32,230
to find out the truth about
his past and what happened?

333
00:16:32,790 --> 00:16:33,950
NARUKI: Yeah, but
that doesn't mean

334
00:16:33,950 --> 00:16:37,710
we should put it in the paper
for everyone to see, does it?

335
00:16:37,710 --> 00:16:39,350
Look, I'm sorry.

336
00:16:39,350 --> 00:16:41,470
I don't mean to make fun of
your profession or anything.

337
00:16:42,630 --> 00:16:45,350
MIFI: No, I understand
what you're saying, Nari.

338
00:16:45,350 --> 00:16:46,150
I want to know.

339
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,830
[GASPING]

340
00:16:47,830 --> 00:16:48,950
I just can't take it!

341
00:16:48,950 --> 00:16:51,950
I want to know
more about Layfee.

342
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:55,070
I have to.

343
00:16:55,070 --> 00:16:57,470
[CHUCKLING]

344
00:17:00,390 --> 00:17:02,870
[SIGH]

345
00:17:07,710 --> 00:17:10,110
[GRUMBLING]

346
00:17:10,110 --> 00:17:12,950
(SIGH) That was a handful.

347
00:17:12,950 --> 00:17:14,790
Mmm.

348
00:17:14,790 --> 00:17:18,790
(BLOWING BUBBLES)

349
00:17:18,790 --> 00:17:20,830
MAN: It's the Kalfa
family attacking us.

350
00:17:23,470 --> 00:17:25,670
WOMAN: Look, this is
the center of Hain City,

351
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:28,550
and it's controlled by one of
the most powerful families.

352
00:17:28,550 --> 00:17:32,430
A war here will destroy the
Kalfas, no doubt about it.

353
00:17:32,430 --> 00:17:34,350
MAN: But they have to believe
they'll come out on top,

354
00:17:34,350 --> 00:17:36,070
or they wouldn't be doing this.

355
00:17:36,070 --> 00:17:36,910
WOMAN: Where's Gadosh?

356
00:17:36,910 --> 00:17:38,630
I want to see him now!

357
00:17:38,630 --> 00:17:40,470
MAN: You took the words
right out of my mouth.

358
00:17:47,350 --> 00:17:48,150
Knock, knock.

359
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:52,910
I don't mind if
you don't get up.

360
00:17:52,910 --> 00:17:56,550
You'll just have to die in bed.

361
00:17:56,550 --> 00:17:57,990
Dude, put some money in.

362
00:17:57,990 --> 00:18:00,670
No way, you haven't paid me
back for the last time yet.

363
00:18:00,670 --> 00:18:02,150
Don't you want to
find out what happens?

364
00:18:02,150 --> 00:18:05,150
Pay up!

365
00:18:05,150 --> 00:18:06,670
[RUSTLING]

366
00:18:06,670 --> 00:18:12,310
Wha‐‐

367
00:18:13,150 --> 00:18:17,190
NARUKI: Mayshen and Layfee, they
live in two different worlds.

368
00:18:17,190 --> 00:18:18,990
If you look at it
realistically, May might

369
00:18:18,990 --> 00:18:21,630
not have a chance of winning.

370
00:18:21,630 --> 00:18:24,110
But regardless, Layfon
is his her first

371
00:18:24,110 --> 00:18:26,110
true love, so I'm
going to stand right

372
00:18:26,110 --> 00:18:27,990
by her side no matter what.

373
00:18:27,990 --> 00:18:30,990
[LAUGHS]

374
00:18:42,430 --> 00:18:45,910
Boy, oh, boy.

375
00:18:53,062 --> 00:18:54,379
Where is he going?

376
00:19:06,830 --> 00:19:08,870
Huh?

377
00:19:08,870 --> 00:19:10,390
There you are.

378
00:19:10,390 --> 00:19:12,150
Layfon!

379
00:19:12,150 --> 00:19:14,870
I'm really sorry for calling
you all the way out here.

380
00:19:14,870 --> 00:19:18,510
Oh, no, I should
apologize‐‐ all those meals.

381
00:19:18,510 --> 00:19:19,390
I'm such an idiot.

382
00:19:19,390 --> 00:19:22,350
But Nina gave me a pretty
good talking to you.

383
00:19:22,350 --> 00:19:24,030
No, it's my fault.
I put them there

384
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:26,190
without even writing my name.

385
00:19:26,190 --> 00:19:30,350
Well, from now on, I'm gonna
eat every last one of them.

386
00:19:30,350 --> 00:19:32,150
(LAUGHS).

387
00:19:32,150 --> 00:19:33,030
(LAUGHING) From now on‐‐

388
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:35,830
I guess that sounds
pretty presumptuous, huh?

389
00:19:35,830 --> 00:19:36,790
(LAUGHING) Mm‐mm.

390
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:45,630
I just‐‐ I just want to know
even more about your past.

391
00:19:45,630 --> 00:19:48,070
Like why did you leave Glendan?

392
00:19:48,070 --> 00:19:49,750
Tell me.

393
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:51,830
You had a Heaven's Blade.

394
00:19:51,830 --> 00:19:53,190
You were a keeper, right?

395
00:19:57,910 --> 00:19:59,670
The reason I left
Glendan is because I

396
00:19:59,670 --> 00:20:03,270
was involved in illegal gambling
and underground tournaments.

397
00:20:03,270 --> 00:20:05,470
Then after I was caught,
I went before the Queen,

398
00:20:05,470 --> 00:20:08,150
and she told me people
with powers as strong

399
00:20:08,150 --> 00:20:10,870
as mine are not
like other humans,

400
00:20:10,870 --> 00:20:13,350
and that fact must
always remain hidden.

401
00:20:13,350 --> 00:20:14,830
[GASP]

402
00:20:14,830 --> 00:20:23,150
I didn't understand it at
the time, but she was right.

403
00:20:23,150 --> 00:20:25,350
Heaven's Blades
are like monsters.

404
00:20:25,350 --> 00:20:28,430
Our powers are greater than
other military artists.

405
00:20:28,430 --> 00:20:30,710
And like a monster,
I abused that power

406
00:20:30,710 --> 00:20:33,390
and went outside the law
without batting an eye.

407
00:20:33,390 --> 00:20:37,830
If people knew what we were
capable of, there'd be panic.

408
00:20:37,830 --> 00:20:39,830
I didn't want to
play by the rules,

409
00:20:39,830 --> 00:20:42,990
and that's why I was
banished from Glendan.

410
00:20:42,990 --> 00:20:47,470
Her mercy saved
me from execution.

411
00:20:47,470 --> 00:20:49,710
I'm nothing more than a monster.

412
00:20:49,710 --> 00:20:51,870
It's OK if you're afraid
of me, Mayshen, because I'd

413
00:20:51,870 --> 00:20:54,950
completely understand that.

414
00:20:54,950 --> 00:20:57,950
[GASPING]

415
00:21:07,390 --> 00:21:11,910
But I'm not afraid.

416
00:21:11,910 --> 00:21:17,350
[CRASHING]

417
00:21:22,350 --> 00:21:23,310
Restoration!

418
00:21:26,030 --> 00:21:26,830
Ah!

419
00:21:31,830 --> 00:21:35,270
[GRUNTING]

420
00:21:38,790 --> 00:21:40,790
Hold on!

421
00:21:40,790 --> 00:21:43,270
Ah!

422
00:21:43,270 --> 00:21:46,230
MAYSHEN: Layfon!

423
00:21:46,230 --> 00:21:52,750
[EXPLOSIONS]

424
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:58,710
Layfee?

425
00:21:58,710 --> 00:22:01,030
Layfee.

426
00:22:01,030 --> 00:22:01,870
Don't worry.

427
00:22:01,870 --> 00:22:02,670
I'm OK.

428
00:22:05,470 --> 00:22:08,030
FELLI: No, you're not
You're not OK at all.

429
00:22:08,030 --> 00:22:08,990
I'm glad.

430
00:22:08,990 --> 00:22:10,110
You actually found me.

431
00:22:10,910 --> 00:22:11,910
FELLI: Of course I did.

432
00:22:11,910 --> 00:22:14,110
Nina and the others
will be here soon.

433
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:15,030
Don't move.

434
00:22:15,030 --> 00:22:17,030
Just stay where you are.

435
00:22:17,030 --> 00:22:19,030
Thank you, Felli.

436
00:22:19,030 --> 00:22:20,510
Thank you.

437
00:22:20,510 --> 00:22:22,230
Layfon!

438
00:22:22,230 --> 00:22:23,030
Layfon?

439
00:22:32,030 --> 00:22:34,830
[SINGING IN JAPANESE]

440
00:23:59,790 --> 00:24:01,790
FELLI: With Layfon
injured, the 17th platoon

441
00:24:01,790 --> 00:24:04,270
gains a surprise replacement
to challenge the first platoon

442
00:24:04,270 --> 00:24:05,190
in competition.

443
00:24:05,190 --> 00:24:08,030
And despite his injuries, I have
to charge Layfon with the task

444
00:24:08,030 --> 00:24:09,510
of a top secret assignment.

445
00:24:09,510 --> 00:24:12,390
Next time "Zuellni Run Amok
and the Contaminoid Offensive"

446
00:24:12,390 --> 00:24:15,110
and restoration.

